# Setup — Adopt KAI in a New Project

## Prerequisites

- Node.js v20+
- Claude Code CLI installed
- Azure DevOps access (org + project)
- For automation hub: AWS CLI v2, Azure CLI

## Quick Setup

```bash
/dx-init          # 1. Core workflow (config, rules, docs, hooks)
/aem-init         # 2. AEM conventions + project seed data (if AEM project)
/auto-init        # 3. Automation agents (optional)
```

Each command detects your environment, asks a few questions, and scaffolds the relevant files.

## What Each Step Does

| Command | Creates | Required? |
|---------|---------|-----------|
| `/dx-init` | `.ai/config.yaml`, `.ai/rules/`, `.ai/docs/`, `.claude/rules/`, `.claude/hooks/` | Yes |
| `/aem-init` | AEM rules in `.claude/rules/`, AEM config in `config.yaml`, project seed data in `.ai/project/` | If AEM project |
| `/auto-init` | `.ai/automation/` (infra.json, prompts, roles, policy) | If you want autonomous agents |

## Automation: Hub vs Consumer

`/auto-init` asks whether this project is a **hub** or **consumer**:

- **Hub** — owns AWS infrastructure + all work-item webhooks. Run `/auto-provision`, `/auto-deploy`, `/auto-pipelines`, `/auto-webhooks`, `/auto-alarms`.
- **Consumer** — gets PR pipelines + delegation-ready pipelines. No AWS needed. Run `/auto-pipelines` only.

For detailed infrastructure setup (Lambda config, pipeline variables, service hooks), see [automation/docs/setup-new-project.md](../automation/docs/setup-new-project.md).

## Verify & Upgrade

```bash
/dx-doctor       # Check all workflow files
/auto-doctor     # Check automation setup (if applicable)
/dx-upgrade      # Upgrade to latest plugin versions
```

All init commands are safe to re-run — they validate against plugin templates and preserve user-customized files.
